{"id":1380,"date":"2021-08-16T06:30:00","date_gmt":"2021-08-16T05:30:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/?p=1380"},"modified":"2021-08-13T17:54:40","modified_gmt":"2021-08-13T16:54:40","slug":"record-breaking-year-continues-for-super-soco-electric","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/record-breaking-year-continues-for-super-soco-electric\/","title":{"rendered":"Record breaking year continues for Super Soco"},"content":{"rendered":"<section class=\"rich-text\">\n\t<div>\n\t\t<div><h2>Super Soco continue to charge ahead in the electric market<\/h2><\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/section><section class=\"rich-text\">\n\t<div>\n\t\t<div><p>Statistics released by the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.mcia.co.uk\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>MCIA<\/strong><\/a> for July have shown continued dominance in the electric bike market for Super Soco with year-to-date registrations continuing to smash records, proving that the appetite for electric has never been higher.<\/p>\n<p>With both consumers and businesses looking at ways to reduce carbon emissions and costs and, as a result, sales are up by a monumental 450% on last year!<\/p>\n<p>In fact, Super Soco currently represents over a quarter of the entire electric motorcycle market and continues to be the leading electric brand in the motorcycle sector by a considerable margin.<\/p>\n<p>In June, Super Soco also became the first electric motorcycle brand to sell over 500 units of one model in a single year with the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/bike\/cpx\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>CPx maxi scooter<\/strong><\/a>, and the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/bike\/tc-max\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>TC Max caf\u00e9 racer-style motorcycle<\/strong><\/a> has also seen a 150% increase in sales compared to 2020.<\/p><\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/section><div class=\"soco-large-image\">\n\t<div><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Super Soco TC Max and CPx electric vehicles in Cornwall\" src=\"https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/Super-Soco-TC-Max-CPx-cornwall.jpg\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/Super-Soco-TC-Max-CPx-cornwall-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/Super-Soco-TC-Max-CPx-cornwall-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/Super-Soco-TC-Max-CPx-cornwall-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/Super-Soco-TC-Max-CPx-cornwall-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/Super-Soco-TC-Max-CPx-cornwall-1500x1000.jpg 1500w\" width=\"2500\" height=\"1667\" \/><\/div>\n<\/div><section class=\"rich-text\">\n\t<div>\n\t\t<div><p>While Super Soco continues to promote its range to existing motorcyclists, we\u2019re also recognising the interest in the brand from non-riders who are keen to make the switch to two wheels. In July, for example, the brand showcased the range at the mecca of all things petrol-powered, the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/join-us-at-the-goodwood-festival-of-speed\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Goodwood Festival of Speed<\/strong><\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>Despite expecting a sceptical reaction from the Goodwood crowd, the Super Soco team found the opposite response, with non-motorcyclists proving very receptive to the brand and the idea of an electric two-wheeler as an alternative transport for urban commuting.<\/p>\n<p>\u201c<em>While our sales figures are looking incredibly strong, we are not resting in our laurels in terms of promoting the brand, both within motorcycling and to a more diverse audience,<\/em>\u201d explains Super Soco UK Marketing and Social Media Manager, James Archibald. \u201c<em>We didn\u2019t know what to expect at Goodwood, but we were very pleasantly surprised. In fact, non-motorcyclists were actually far more open to the idea of electric vehicles than motorcyclists tend to be and needed very little convincing of the benefits of EV ownership.<\/em><\/p>\n<p><em>\u201cWe came away feeling really positive about the future of electric motorcycles and scooters and with a good number of leads for people wanting to test ride the Super Soco models throughout our dealer network. The event showed us that there is a real market out there for non-riders looking to switch to two wheels, which is great news for the industry overall.<\/em>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>To find out more about the current range and to arrange a test ride, please visit a Super Soco stockist. You can find the nearest showroom with our <a href=\"https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/dealers\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Dealer Locator<\/strong><\/a>.<\/p><\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n<\/section><div class=\"soco-large-image\">\n\t<div><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Super soco at the Goodwood Festival of Speed\" src=\"https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/Goodwood-news-story.jpg\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/Goodwood-news-story-300x167.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/Goodwood-news-story-1024x569.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/Goodwood-news-story-768x427.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/Goodwood-news-story-1536x854.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/www.supersoco.co.uk\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/07\/Goodwood-news-story-1799x1000.jpg 1799w\" width=\"2400\" height=\"1334\" \/><\/div>\n<\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Statistics released by the MCIA for July have shown continued dominance in the electric bike market for Super Soco with year-to-date registrations continuing to smash records, proving that the appetite for electric has never been higher.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":1383,"comment_status":"closed","ping_sta